## Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `model` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | `claude-3-5-haiku-20241022` | The model to use for file analysis |
| `messages` | array | ‚úÖ Yes | - | Array of message objects for the conversation. Each message must have a role (user or assistant) and content. Content can include: - Text blocks with type "text" - Document blocks with type "document" containing: - source: Object with type "base64" or "url" - For base64: media_type (e.g., "application/pdf") and data (base64 string) - For url: url field with the file URL Supported file formats: PDF, DOCX, XLSX, TXT, CSV, JSON, XML, HTML Maximum file size: 20MB Example with URL: ```json [ { "role": "user", "content": [ { "type": "text", "text": "Please analyze this document" }, { "type": "document", "source": { "type": "url", "url": "https://example.com/document.pdf" } } ] } ] ``` Example with base64: ```json [ { "role": "user", "content": [ { "type": "text", "text": "Please analyze this document" }, { "type": "document", "source": { "type": "base64", "media_type": "application/pdf", "data": "JVBERi0xLjQKJeLjz9MK..." } } ] } ] ``` |
| `max_tokens` | integer | ‚úÖ Yes | `1024` | The maximum number of tokens to generate before stopping |
| `temperature` | number | ‚ùå No | `1.0` | Amount of randomness injected into the response. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0 |
| `top_p` | number | ‚ùå No | `1.0` | Use nucleus sampling. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0 |
| `top_k` | integer | ‚ùå No | `null` | Only sample from the top K options for each subsequent token |
| `stream` | boolean | ‚ùå No | `false` | Whether to incrementally stream the response using server-sent events |
| `stop_sequences` | array | ‚ùå No | - | Custom text sequences that will cause the model to stop generating |

### Messages Array Structure

Each message object in the `messages` array should have the following structure:

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `role` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | The role of the message. Can be: `user`, `assistant`, or `system` |
| `content` | array/string | ‚úÖ Yes | The content of the message |

### Content Array Structure (when content is an array)

| Field | Type | Required | Example | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `type` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | `text` | The type of content |
| `text` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | `"The positive prompt for the generation."` | The text content when type is `text` |

