## Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Range | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------|-------------|
| `model` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` | - | The model identifier. Use `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` for this model |
| `messages` | array | ‚úÖ Yes | - | - | Input messages for the conversation. Each message must have a `role` (user/assistant) and `content`. Content can include text blocks or document blocks with base64 or URL sources. Supported formats: PDF, DOCX, XLSX, TXT, CSV, JSON, XML, HTML. Max file size: 20MB. See [Messages Structure](#messages-structure) below for details |
| `max_tokens` | integer | ‚úÖ Yes | - | 1-64000 | Maximum number of tokens to generate. The model may stop before reaching this limit |
| `temperature` | number | ‚ùå No | `1.0` | 0.0-1.0 | Controls randomness in output. Use lower values (closer to 0.0) for analytical tasks, higher values (closer to 1.0) for creative tasks. Note: Even at 0.0, results are not fully deterministic |
| `top_p` | number | ‚ùå No | - | 0.0-1.0 | Nucleus sampling threshold. Controls diversity by considering only tokens with cumulative probability up to top_p. Recommended for advanced use only. Do not use with temperature |
| `top_k` | integer | ‚ùå No | - | >0 | Only sample from the top K options for each token. Removes low probability responses. Recommended for advanced use only |
| `stream` | boolean | ‚ùå No | `false` | - | Whether to stream the response incrementally using server-sent events |
| `stop_sequences` | array | ‚ùå No | - | Max 8191 sequences | Custom text sequences that will cause the model to stop generating. Each sequence must contain non-whitespace characters |

### Messages Structure

**Basic structure:**
```json
{
  "role": "user",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Please analyze this document"
    },
    {
      "type": "document",
      "source": {
        "type": "url",
        "url": "https://example.com/document.pdf"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**With Base64:**
```json
{
  "type": "document",
  "source": {
    "type": "base64",
    "media_type": "application/pdf",
    "data": "JVBERi0xLjQK..."
  }
}
```

### Messages Array Structure

Each message object in the `messages` array should have the following structure:

| Field | Type | Required | Range | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------|-------------|
| `role` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | The role of the message. Can be: `user` or `assistant` |
| `content` | array/string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | The content of the message. Can be a string or an array of content blocks |

### Content Block Structure

When `content` is an array, each element can be one of the following types:

#### Text Content Block

| Field | Type | Required | Range | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------|-------------|
| `type` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | Must be `text` |
| `text` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | The text content |

#### Document Content Block

| Field | Type | Required | Range | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------|-------------|
| `type` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | Must be `document` |
| `source` | object | ‚úÖ Yes | - | The document source (base64 or URL) |

#### Document Source Structure (URL)

| Field | Type | Required | Range | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------|-------------|
| `type` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | Must be `url` |
| `url` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | The URL of the document file |

#### Document Source Structure (Base64)

| Field | Type | Required | Range | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------|-------------|
| `type` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | Must be `base64` |
| `media_type` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | The MIME type of the document (e.g., `application/pdf`, `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document`) |
| `data` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | Base64-encoded document data |

### Supported Document Formats

| Format | MIME Type | Extension |
|--------|-----------|-----------|
| PDF | `application/pdf` | `.pdf` |
| Word | `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document` | `.docx` |
| Excel | `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet` | `.xlsx` |
| Plain Text | `text/plain` | `.txt` |
| CSV | `text/csv` | `.csv` |
| JSON | `application/json` | `.json` |
| XML | `application/xml` or `text/xml` | `.xml` |
| HTML | `text/html` | `.html` |

**Note**: Maximum file size is 20MB.

