| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Range | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------|-------------|
| `model` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | `claude-opus-4-5-20251101` | - | The model to use for the request. `claude-opus-4-5-20251101` |
| `messages` | array | ‚úÖ Yes | - | - | Array of message objects for the conversation. Each message must have a `role` (user/assistant) and `content` (string or array of content blocks) |
| `max_tokens` | integer | ‚úÖ Yes | - | 1-64000 | Maximum number of tokens to generate in the response |
| `temperature` | number | ‚ùå No | `1.0` | 0.0-2.0 | Controls randomness in output. Use lower values (closer to 0.0) for analytical tasks, higher values (closer to 2.0) for creative tasks |
| `top_p` | number | ‚ùå No | - | 0.0-1.0 | Nucleus sampling threshold. Controls diversity by considering only tokens with cumulative probability up to top_p. Recommended for advanced use only. Do not use with temperature |
| `top_k` | integer | ‚ùå No | - | >0 | Only sample from the top K options for each token. Removes low probability responses. Recommended for advanced use only |
| `stream` | boolean | ‚ùå No | `false` | - | Whether to stream the response incrementally using server-sent events |
| `stop` | array | ‚ùå No | - | Max 8191 sequences | Custom text sequences that will cause the model to stop generating. Each sequence must contain non-whitespace characters |
| `presence_penalty` | number | ‚ùå No | `0` | -2.0 to 2.0 | Positive values penalize new tokens based on whether they appear in the text so far |
| `frequency_penalty` | number | ‚ùå No | `0` | -2.0 to 2.0 | Positive values penalize new tokens based on their existing frequency in the text so far |

### Messages Array Structure

Each message object in the `messages` array should have the following structure:

| Field | Type | Required | Range | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------|-------------|
| `role` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | The role of the message. Can be: `user` or `assistant` |
| `content` | array/string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | The content of the message. Can be a simple string for text-only messages, or an array of content blocks for multimodal content |

### Content Block Structure (when content is an array)

| Field | Type | Required | Range | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------|-------------|
| `type` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | Must be `text` |
| `text` | string | ‚úÖ Yes | - | The text content |

